# Design System (Book 02)

**Law:** `docs/foundation/NERTURA_CORE.md` · `docs/foundation/02-design-system/` · Architecture: `15-design-system-architecture.md`

Before any UI change: read **Nertura Core** → identify Book 02 chapter → cite in compliance report.

## CSS import rule (non-negotiable)

- App `layout.tsx` → **only** `import './globals.css'`
- App `globals.css` → **only** `@import "@nertura/ui/globals.css"`
- **Never** import `@nertura/ui/globals.css` or `@nertura/ui/styles/globals.css` directly in app layouts
- Run `pnpm check:css-imports` before shipping UI changes

## One design language

Marketing · dashboard · Doctor · map · admin · Growth AI share `@nertura/ui` tokens and patterns.

- Use `@nertura/ui` components and tokens (`void`, `signal`, shadcn HSL vars) — **no one-off visual styles**
- Do **not** change logo or primary green (`signal` / `#2DDAAF`) without product approval
- **Mobile first** → tablet → desktop

## Copy & language

- **No mixed-language UI** in one flow (`tr` | `en` via copy maps / locale)
- **No technical user-facing copy** — friendly farmer language; log details server-side

## Surface rules

| Surface | Rule |
|---------|------|
| **Map** | Desktop: ~73% map / ~27% panel; mobile: bottom-sheet / capped panel scroll (Book 02 Ch. 08) |
| **AI Doctor** | Conversation-first composer; short-first answers (Book 02 Ch. 07) |
| **Free users** | Minimal navigation; premium **locked**, not hidden |
| **States** | Empty, loading, error, success per Book 02 Ch. 11 — info cards over red alarms where appropriate |

